    {
      "id": "PopularPost60573",
      "post_content": "Anyone complaining something like \"This card sucks since on turn 3 my opponent always has like at least 6 cards.\" is a moron. It's rather obvious cards like these are meant to fit the tempo of black discard. Using cheap early cards like [Duress](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Duress) this can easily be a 4/4 or higher by turn 3, and then probably only getting stronger as turns go by.",
      "posted_by": "BrutalJim",
